title: 4 more arrested in 'Operation Who's Next' drug sting
text:
PLAQUEMINES PARISH, LA (WVUE) - The Plaquemines Parish Sheriff's Office made four more arrests in connection with a sweeping drug sting called "Operation Who's Next."
William Dixon was arrested Tuesday at his Belle Chasse residence and Leandro Gaytan-Dopico surrendered to deputies at the Belle Chasse Lockup.
The year-long, undercover drug operation has resulted in 49 arrests on numerous charges of buying and selling illegal narcotics
Five defendants remain at large. They are John Billiot, Jr., Natosha Dailey, Jonathan Hingle, Cynthia Johnson and Jeremy Keller.
Corey Picquet and Leslie Roberts were taken into custody Wednesday morning in Iowa, LA near Lake Charles.
Anyone with information on the location of the wanted at-large defendants is asked to call the PPSO Narcotics Division at 504-297-5315 or the Dispatch Center at 504-564-2525.
